snippet.textDisplay: Last Wednesday I re-did my sisters hair. She went to a "professional" at a salon, paid $85 and her roots were RED while the rest of her hair was still really dark. I bleached only the bottom of her hair with 20 vol developer and it lighten to what the top color was. I was able to fix her hair and I was so proud of myself. I felt so professional. I was like, yass, this is my career now.

snippet.textDisplay: I dyed my hair dark red for a year then wanted to go back to my natural colour which is blonde so I used 2 colour strippers, 2 powder  bleach, then added a blonde dye, the next day I powder bleached it again twice because it was still bright orange! When I was washing the last bleach session out my hair was like chewing gum and was coming out in clumps, I cried, run to the hairdresser with a towel on my head, all they could do was brush and cut through the matted stuck mass of hair and I ended up with hair up to my chin (it was to my waist at the beginning) my hair was still orange, I wasn't aloud to touch my hair with any colour for 6 weeks. I was lucky though, I didnt get any bald patches. I can laugh now but at the time I cried so bad 🤣🤣

snippet.textDisplay: I remember bleaching my hair at home when I was 16.... yeah its was bad.. (note: my hair was very dark naturally, almost black.)  I had grown my hair out to about my belly button and bleached the ends up until about my shoulders. (very good thing I didnt do anything past that.) my hair ended up being rubber and practically elastic to the point where I could stretch my hair. Since I hated it so much my hair was always up in a bun for months which broke alot of my hair and left very short hairs by my forehead. So I ended up cutting to shoulder length which was heart breaking since I loved my long hair so much. Years later I had cut it a few times, had horrific bangs but eventually I went and got my hair professionally done which cost me about $400 My hair is still as healthy as every and almost to my belly button again.
